## Grid System

Use a 12-column grid (`grid-cols-12`) for section-level layouts. Avoid simplified shorthand grids like `grid-cols-2` or `grid-cols-4` at the section level because they couple column count to item count and break cross-section alignment.

**Exception:** Equal three-column layouts may use `grid-cols-3` directly when all items are identical width and no mixed-width slots are needed (e.g. step cards, team cards).

**How:** Declare `grid-cols-12` on the wrapper; assign `col-span-*` on each child.
- 2-up → `col-span-6`
- 3-up → `col-span-4` (or `grid-cols-3` for pure equal layouts)
- 4-up → `col-span-3`
- Mixed → e.g. `col-span-8` + `col-span-4`

Apply responsive breakpoints on `col-span` (not on the grid container) to handle mobile stacking:
```
<div className="grid grid-cols-12 gap-8">
 <div className="col-span-12 sm:col-span-6 lg:col-span-4">...</div>
</div>
```

